Hungary to Phase Out Tax Breaks for Employees, Napi Reports

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-04-20T06:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/hungary-to-phase-out-tax-breaks-for-employees-napi-reports.html
Hungary plans to phase out tax
breaks for full-time employees from next year in order to boost
 tax revenue ,  Napi Gazdasag  said, citing the countryâ€™s euro
convergence program.  The gradual elimination of tax breaks would save the budget
180 billion forint ($975 million) next year and 230 billion
forint in 2013, according to the newspaper.  The move would raise the tax burden of employees earning up
to 230,000 forint a month and the personal income tax for on the
minimum wage earners would increase to 16 percent by 2014 from
under 3 percent in 2009, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
